  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is a cluster-randomized trial of nursing homes to assess whether decolonization with
      routine chlorhexidine bathing and periodic use of nasal antiseptics can reduce
      hospitalizations associated with infections, antibiotic utilization, and multi-drug resistant
      organism (MDRO) prevalence. The comparator arm will be routine bathing care.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
